>By the way, Tom, it looks like your pre-heat hose just hangs open at
>its lower end. It should run down through the rear tin to a 1-inch
>intake pipe that gets bolted to the lower, left-rear area of your
>engine, to grab engine cooling air on its way out of the tin.

That's the set-up on my '64.  The engine is a '68 Beetle 1500, but
the tin and pre-heat arrangement corresponds to the pre-'67 Bus
configuration.

